The paper discusses the use of generative deep learning networks and reinforcement learning for optimizing chemical molecule generation, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of deep learning networks for molecular structure generation also involves computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL) techniques. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of curriculum learning, which is a technique commonly used in supervised learning (cs.SD).
